mmary_text\",\"text\":\"**Resolving configuration issues**\\n\\nI’m running into an issue with version 3.1.5, which is the only active version available. However, because of some current problems with 3.1.4, I’m not totally sure if I should proceed. I might need to add a NoConfigureObjectMapper. I’m considering if I could duplicate the serialization or extend a utility. But, wait, I realize I can't extend ObjectMapper directly, which complicates things. It’s a bit tricky!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_EBPrNhmVUDXJfbGkTmMojPkN|fc_053c9c0e976b369b0169f960c4d958819696d1ddfba7f09888", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.thymeleaf/thymeleaf/3.1.5.RELEASE/src/test/java/tools/jackson/databind/NoConfigureObjectMapper.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage tools.jackson.databind;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.Writer;\nimport java.text.DateFormat;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\nimport tools.jackson.core.json.JsonWriteFeature;\n\npublic class NoConfigureObjectMapper {\n\n    private final JsonFactory factory = new JsonFactory();\n    private DateFormat dateFormat;\n\n    public NoConfigureObjectMapper() {\n    }\n\n    public void findAndRegisterModules() {\n    }\n\n    public NoConfigureObjectMapper disable(SerializationFeature feature) {\n        return this;\n    }\n\n    public JsonFactory getFactory() {\n        return this.factory;\n    }\n\n    public void setDateFormat(DateFormat dateFormat) {\n        this.dateFormat = dateFormat;\n    }\n\n    public DateFormat getDateFormat() {\n        return this.dateFormat;\n    }\n\n    public void writeValue(Writer writer, Object object) throws IOException {\n        if (object instanceof Map<?, ?> map) {\n            writer.write('{');\n            boolean first = true;\n            for (Map.Entry<?, ?> entry : map.entrySet()) {\n                if (first) {\n                    first = false;\n                } else {\n                    writer.write(',');\n                }\n                writer.write('\"');\n                writer.write(entry.getKey().toString());\n                writer.write(\"\\\":\\\"\");\n                writer.write(entry.getValue().toString());\n                writer.write('\"');\n            }\n            writer.write('}');\n        } else {\n            writer.write(String.valueOf(object));\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class JsonFactory {\n\n        public void configure(JsonWriteFeature feature, boolean state) {\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 893, "output": 1539, "cacheRead": 62464, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 64896, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777950900497, "responseId": "resp_053c9c0e976b369b0169f960b5756481968c03356ef3003cd6"}}
